 Editor's note: This live event has ended. You can watch it in the video above. PRETORIA - Former president Thabo Mbeki is inaugurated as chancellor of the University of South Africa on Monday morning.Mbeki replaces Judge Bernard Ngoepe, who served as chancellor for 15 years.The university says it's excited about the value Mbeki's stature and intellectual standing will add to the institution.Higher Education Minister Blade Nzimande and Vice-chancellor Professor Mandla Makhanya will be amongst the speakers.eNCA